 Research Engineer 
 
 Job description: 
 
Research Engineer positions offered by Ford Motor Company (Dearborn, MI). Research and develop advanced control techniques, such as Model Predictive Control, Adaptive Control, Optimal Control, and Intelligent Control, to enable innovative automotive technologies and in-vehicle features. Support the research, development, and validation of robust algorithms according to Fordâ€™s engineering requirements to design automotive features. Support the analysis of system behavior and plant modeling, monitor signal processing, including real-time data processing from on-board systems, as well as monitor cloud and vehicle-to-vehicle based sources. Design control methods through Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning and utilize Engine Mapping & Automated Calibration and engineering optimization methods to enhance Ford features. 
 
 Minimum Requirements: 
Masterâ€™s or foreign equivalent degree in automotive systems engineering, electrical engineering, mechanical engineering or a related field including thesis work on controls, system identification, advanced estimation, or optimization applied to automotive or similar industrial applications. 
Education or experience must include using C, MATLAB, Simulink, Stateflow, Real Time Workshop, or dSpace. 
Experience may be, but need not be, acquired concurrently
